songs.comment_text: I was addicted to drugs and alcohol. I had no hope left, I had lost the will to live. He saved me and I will love Him forever for that. He's showed himself to me through many spiritual experiences in the last 40 days that I've been sober. I've been transformed into a new creation. He can do the same thing in your life. Jesus can save you too. Invite Him into your heart and never look back. I was lost but now I'm found.

To those on the fence about whether to live for Jesus, for the backsliden one who is listening to this, to the one away from God but listening to worship because of the peace it gives them.
Jesus wants you to surrender your heart. Don't be away from His love. He misses you.
As a Christian all my life, I was on fire and then enter my very attractive ex-partner - I backslid. I did drugs, had sex with very good looking men, was popular, partyied, was an adrenaline junkie, hill bombing skate boarder. 
And still, NOTHING compared to Jesus. His presence. His peace. The Holy Spirit. His love. It drew me back, now His love, joy and peace are my banner.
Time is short and hell is real but God's arms are open wide.
Pray(Aloud is best if you are comfortable) "Jesus, I need you. Please forgive me of my sins and come into my heart. I give my life to follow You and to live for You daily. Thank you Lord that You hear me, You are faithful and You love me'.
Thank you, God is so pleased with you.
Continue on by reading His word, getting good Christian friends and being established in a good church and to grow in Christ become sensitive to His voice by being obedient when He speaks to you gently about cutting certain things out of your life.
God bless!

songs.song: Debussy: Suite bergamasque, CD 82, L. 75: III. Clair de lune (Arr. Roelens for Violin and Piano)
songs.post_title: Late Night Songs Playlist: Best Night Music for Sleep (Playlist Updated in 2025)
songs.comment_text:
I was lucky enough to be born into a house with music. 

My dad loves to play piano, and he wasn‚Äôt the most talkative person, but when he started to play piano, you could feel him speaking to you. 

When I was 2 years old, he would sit me on his lap and play this song. When I was 14 years old, he was diagnosed with cancer, and they told him he wouldn‚Äôt live to the end of the year (it was August)

He lived for two more years, defying everything the doctors had told him. 

He died surrounded by his family, and his last words to me were, ‚Äúnever stop playing, can you please, play for me? And not forget me? Can you do that for me?‚Äù 

At his funeral, I was asked if I would play a song, and I chose to play this song, the song he played while I would sit on his lap. The song that could bring back a thousand memories. 

And now, 8 years later, I sat down at the piano with my beautiful 2 year old girl, who we decided to name Claire, and played this song for her.

songs.comment_text: This is probably insane to think about but one of the only things that kept me going on when I was at my lowest point was when I started to notice the beauty in this world. Songs like these, summer rain and snow,  sunsets and starry nights. I realised that there‚Äôs so much I want to do and visit before I leave this world. I want to feel every possible feeling and keep adrenaline in my system. And when I noticed these things and I thought hard about what I wanted to do with myself and my life, I changed as a person. I became more ambitious and wanted to pick up a book for the first time in my life, learn the piano maybe pick up a language. And it changed everything...but it really did all start with this song.
